-- ============================================================
-- Industrial Fiber Laser Cutting Parameters - Thick Materials
-- Generated: 2026-06-27
-- ============================================================
-- Coverage: 10-30mm carbon steel, stainless steel 304/316/316L, HRPO
-- Power levels: 1kW, 2kW, 3kW, 4kW, 6kW, 8kW, 10kW, 12kW, 15kW, 20kW
--
-- Sources:
--   1. Trumpf TruLaser series application data (published cut charts)
--      URL: https://www.trumpf.com/en_US/products/machines-systems/laser-cutting-machines/
--   2. Bystronic ByStar Fiber published cutting parameters
--      URL: https://www.bystronic.com/en/products/laser-cutting-systems/
--   3. IPG Photonics YLS series application notes
--      URL: https://www.ipgphotonics.com/en/applications/materials-processing/cutting
--   4. Bodor i-Series published parameter tables
--      URL: https://www.bodor.com/fiber-laser-cutting-machine.html
--   5. HSG Laser G3015A cutting data sheets
--      URL: https://www.hsglaser.com/
--   6. Raycus RFL-C series application parameters
--      URL: https://www.raycuslaser.com/
--   7. Amada ENSIS fiber laser published data
--      URL: https://www.amada.com/america/
--   8. Mazak OPTIPLEX published specifications
--      URL: https://www.mazakoptonics.com/
--   9. Precitec ProCutter application data
--      URL: https://www.precitec.com/
--   10. The Fabricator magazine - fiber laser thick cutting articles
--      URL: https://www.thefabricator.com/
--
-- Parameter conventions:
--   - All speeds in mm/min
--   - Gas pressure in bar
--   - Focus position: negative = below surface, positive = above
--   - power_pct = 100 for CW (continuous wave) industrial cutting
--   - thickness_mm = actual material thickness
--   - Nozzle types: single (low pressure N2/air) or double (high pressure O2)
--
-- Notes on gas selection:
--   - O2 (oxygen): exothermic reaction, faster on carbon steel, oxide edge
--   - N2 (nitrogen): clean cut, no oxidation, slower, used for stainless/aluminum
--   - Air: economy option, slight oxidation, used for thin carbon steel
-- ============================================================

-- ============================================================
-- CARBON STEEL (Mild Steel / A36 / S235-S355) with O2 assist
-- Source: Trumpf TruLaser 5030 fiber / Bystronic ByStar Fiber
-- ============================================================

