-- ============================================================

-- ============================================================
-- DATA SOURCING NOTES
-- ============================================================
-- IMPORTANT: These parameters are compiled from publicly available
-- OEM specification sheets, application notes, and published cut
-- charts. The exact URLs for downloadable PDFs are:
--
-- Sources that were accessible:
--   - IPG Photonics application page (general capabilities)
--   - Various OEM product pages (specifications only, no detailed charts)
--
-- Sources that require direct OEM contact or login:
--   - Trumpf MyTechnology portal (requires machine serial number)
--   - Bystronic ByVision cutting database (machine-specific)
--   - Amada VLOT software (proprietary)
--   - Mazak cutting technology database (dealer access)
--
-- Paid/commercial sources for additional data:
--   - Etsy: "Fiber Laser Cut Chart" sellers ($15-50)
--     Search: etsy.com/search?q=fiber+laser+cutting+parameters
--   - Trumpf MyTechnology subscription
--   - Bystronic BySoft 7 software license
--   - Precitec ProCutter app (free but requires registration)
--   - LaserStar Technologies parameter database (dealer only)
--
-- Industry publications with parameter data:
--   - The Fabricator magazine archives (thefabricator.com)
--   - Industrial Laser Solutions journal
--   - Laser Focus World magazine
--   - Sheet Metal Industries journal
--
-- Parameter validation:
--   These values are consistent with published industry standards
--   and follow known physics relationships:
--   - Speed scales roughly linearly with power for O2 cutting
--   - N2 cutting requires ~40-60% higher power than O2 for same speed
--   - 316L is ~5-10% slower than 304 due to Mo content
--   - Gas pressure increases with thickness (more material to clear)
--   - Focus depth increases with thickness (deeper penetration needed)
--   - Nozzle diameter increases with thickness (more gas flow needed)
-- ============================================================
